International News.

Park Avenue at S. W. corner of 67th Street, showing The Sulgrave, s
new apartment hotel at 56 east 67th Street.
The old house on the corner will be demolished in the autumn of 1929,
to make place for a garden for the hotel.
About 1924.

Park Avenue, south on west side from 71st Street to 67st; Street, on Lenox Pill, showing old Presbyterien Hospital between 7lst and 70th, shortly before its demolition. On north west corner of 71st may be seen part of the G.S. Brewster residence, which will be demolished in 1929, end in the south west corner of 74th Street the George S.
Blumenthal residence.
March 31, 1928.
P.L. Sperr,Photcgrapher.

67th Street, south side, between Park and Lexington Avenues. This apartment house was erected on the former site of the Baptist Home for the aged. A.S. Thomas was the architect for the new
building.
About 1930.
George E. Van Anda.
